sec.p:
Participant’s fluid balance was assessed by measuring nude body mass pre- and post-match, as well as pre- and post-bathroom use (to monitor toilet breaks). After baseline measurements, fluid intake was monitored using individualized bottles, with participants instructed not to spit, spill or shower with water from them and measuring remaining fluid in the bottle post-match. Sweat loss (not corrected for gas exchange) was then calculated accordingly [40]:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\text{Sweat Loss }} = {\text{ Weight}}_{{{\mathrm{Baseline}}}} - {\text{ Weight}}_{{{\mathrm{Post}}}} + {\text{ Fluid Intake }} - {\text{ Urine Loss}}$$\end{document}Sweat Loss=WeightBaseline-WeightPost+Fluid Intake-Urine Loss
